  <front>
   <head>[Epitaph on Mrs Clerke]</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Lo! where this silent marble weeps,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A friend, a wife, a mother sleeps:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A heart, within whose sacred cell</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The peaceful virtues loved to dwell.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Affection warm, and faith sincere,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And soft humanity were there.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In agony, in death, resigned,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">She felt the wound she left behind.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Her infant image, here below,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Sits smiling on a father's woe:</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whom what awaits, while yet he strays</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Along the lonely vale of days?</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A pang, to secret sorrow dear;</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A sigh; an unavailing tear;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Till time shall every grief remove,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With life, with memory, and with love.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
